What you need to know:

The most memorable one is of course the much-talked-about Oliech thunderbolt against Cape Verde in 2003 at Kasarani that earned Harambee Stars a place in the 2004 Africa Cup of Nations in Tunisia after a 12-year hiatusOliech had already won many hearts after he famously turned down an offer from the Qatari government to change nationalities for a jaw-dropping cash incentiveMany years later, Oliech says he would gleefully seize the opportunity, without a second thought, given another chance